52.4	Robert_Shiller	Robert J. Shiller	Robert James "Bob" Shiller (born Detroit, Michigan, March 29, 1946) is an American economist, academic, and best-selling author. He currently serves as the Arthur M. Okun Professor of Economics at Yale University and is a Fellow at the Yale International Center for Finance, Yale School of Management. Shiller has been a research associate of the National Bureau of Economic Research (NBER) since 1980, was Vice President of the American Economic Association in 2005, and President of the Eastern Economic Association for 2006-2007. He is also the co-founder and chief economist of the investment management firm MacroMarkets LLC.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/Robert_Shiller_-_World_Economic_Forum_Annual_Meeting_2012.jpg/220px-Robert_Shiller_-_World_Economic_Forum_Annual_Meeting_2012.jpg
